WEBVTT

1
00:00:01.435 --> 00:00:02.960
<i>('80s ROCK PLAYING)</i>

2
00:00:07.841 --> 00:00:10.276
<i>And I ran</i>

3
00:00:10.344 --> 00:00:13.314
<i>I ran so far away</i>

4
00:00:14.581 --> 00:00:19.451
<i>I just ran I ran
all night and day</i>

5
00:00:19.520 --> 00:00:20.749
(CHILDREN SCREAMING)

6
00:00:25.425 --> 00:00:26.586
Do you think he saw us?

7
00:00:26.660 --> 00:00:27.958
(SHRIEKS)

8
00:00:28.428 --> 00:00:29.657
What up. dipwads?

9
00:00:29.730 --> 00:00:32.222
Oh. no! Jimmy Nickles!

10
00:00:32.666 --> 00:00:33.895
Give me the money!

11
00:00:33.967 --> 00:00:35.144
Actually. we
didn't bring it today.

12
00:00:35.168 --> 00:00:36.363
Here you go.

13
00:00:36.436 --> 00:00:37.699
Gus!

14
00:00:37.771 --> 00:00:38.795
Give it up. Spencer.

15
00:00:38.872 --> 00:00:41.050
or I'll shove a Jimmy Nickle
sandwich right in your grill.

16
00:00:41.074 --> 00:00:43.441
I think it's a knuckle sandwich.

17
00:00:43.510 --> 00:00:44.876
Okay. Okay.

18
00:00:46.179 --> 00:00:48.114
And from the KangaROOS?

19
00:00:51.618 --> 00:00:53.018
See you tomorrow. butt munches.

20
00:00:53.086 --> 00:00:55.317
It's sloppy joes and tater tots.

21
00:00:56.390 --> 00:00:59.758
You know. Gus. one of these days
we're gonna stand up to Jimmy Nickles.

22
00:00:59.826 --> 00:01:02.421
Yeah. I think I'll stay
home sick that day.

23
00:01:02.496 --> 00:01:04.158
(BELL RINGS)

24
00:01:05.666 --> 00:01:07.191
SHAWN: It's about time.

25
00:01:07.267 --> 00:01:09.293
Sit down. I have troubling news.

26
00:01:09.369 --> 00:01:12.168
You forgot to TiVo <i>America's
Next Top Model.</i> didn't you?

27
00:01:12.239 --> 00:01:14.037
Why is it so hard to
set the Season Pass?

28
00:01:14.107 --> 00:01:15.575
It's not <i>Top Model</i> related.

29
00:01:16.743 --> 00:01:17.767
What is it?

30
00:01:17.844 --> 00:01:19.710
Jimmy Nicholas called.

31
00:01:20.047 --> 00:01:21.606
Jimmy Nickles called us?

32
00:01:21.682 --> 00:01:23.480
From where? Prison?

33
00:01:23.584 --> 00:01:25.678
I don't think so. It
didn't sound like it.

34
00:01:25.752 --> 00:01:27.530
What does prison sound
like? Is there singing?

35
00:01:27.554 --> 00:01:29.523
Shawn! I don't know.
He left a message.

36
00:01:29.590 --> 00:01:30.888
Don't you dare return that call.

37
00:01:30.958 --> 00:01:34.122
I don't need to. He's
coming here in five minutes.

38
00:01:36.997 --> 00:01:38.989
Jimmy Nickles is coming
here? In five minutes?

39
00:01:39.066 --> 00:01:40.159
Yeah.

40
00:01:40.601 --> 00:01:44.538
Okay. okay. We can handle
this. We can handle this.

41
00:01:45.305 --> 00:01:47.150
I'm gonna go print out
a fake foreclosure notice

42
00:01:47.174 --> 00:01:48.351
and stick it on the front door.

43
00:01:48.375 --> 00:01:49.452
And then we both can go outside

44
00:01:49.476 --> 00:01:51.120
and scrape the "Psych"
sign off the front window.

45
00:01:51.144 --> 00:01:54.410
Gus. I think we can afford to relax
a little bit. He said he wants to talk.

46
00:01:54.481 --> 00:01:57.246
And by "talk" I hope he means
talk. not my head in a toilet.

47
00:01:57.317 --> 00:01:58.512
He's gonna try and kill us.

48
00:01:58.585 --> 00:02:00.349
He's not gonna kill us.

49
00:02:00.420 --> 00:02:01.581
Right?

50
00:02:01.655 --> 00:02:02.884
I mean. people change.

51
00:02:02.956 --> 00:02:04.534
We haven't seen him
since the fifth grade.

52
00:02:04.558 --> 00:02:06.356
I don't need to see him. Shawn.

53
00:02:06.426 --> 00:02:08.054
Some people are just born evil.

54
00:02:08.128 --> 00:02:11.530
The kid from <i>The Omen.</i> the <i>Children
of the Corn.</i> Chad Michael Murray.

55
00:02:13.600 --> 00:02:14.624
What is this?

56
00:02:14.701 --> 00:02:16.670
Ooh. eBay.

57
00:02:16.737 --> 00:02:18.069
Auto bid!

58
00:02:18.138 --> 00:02:21.666
600 bucks plus a penny.
The penny is the trick.

59
00:02:21.742 --> 00:02:24.075
I got in a full-on bidding
war with a Montessori school.

60
00:02:24.144 --> 00:02:25.976
What do we need a
locker in the office for?

61
00:02:26.046 --> 00:02:29.107
First of all. I have nowhere
to put my sociology textbook.

62
00:02:29.182 --> 00:02:30.377
And...

63
00:02:32.152 --> 00:02:33.792
(WHISPERING
DRAMATICALLY) Chicka-chickahh!

64
00:02:35.922 --> 00:02:38.653
You always gotta hit it
right on the nose. don't you?

65
00:02:38.725 --> 00:02:40.455
Why couldn't I be Crockett?

66
00:02:41.128 --> 00:02:44.155
'Cause. Gus. you stood in front of
the entire third-grade class and said.

67
00:02:44.231 --> 00:02:46.723
"When I grow up. I wanna
be Philip Michael Thomas."

68
00:02:46.800 --> 00:02:49.312
Well. you said you wanted to be
the mascot for the Milwaukee Brewers.

69
00:02:49.336 --> 00:02:50.947
Dude. he's the biggest
sausage in the world.

70
00:02:50.971 --> 00:02:53.099
Why is Jimmy Nickles
coming here. Shawn?

71
00:02:53.173 --> 00:02:54.698
How big is he now? I don't know.

72
00:02:54.775 --> 00:02:56.175
Why couldn't you
be a real psychic?

73
00:02:56.243 --> 00:02:57.643
(KNOCKING ON DOOR)

74
00:02:57.711 --> 00:02:58.911
JIMMY: Hey. you guys in there?

75
00:02:58.979 --> 00:03:00.607
Oh. God. that's him.

76
00:03:01.348 --> 00:03:02.992
He's not getting my lunch
money. I'll tell you that much.

77
00:03:03.016 --> 00:03:05.328
Great. You can terrify him
with your Wally Joyner mini-bat.

78
00:03:05.352 --> 00:03:06.843
Open the door.

79
00:03:18.331 --> 00:03:19.822
What up. boys?

80
00:03:27.107 --> 00:03:29.147
(WHISPERING) That was
a good call with the mini-bat.

81
00:03:34.781 --> 00:03:38.218
<i>I know. you know That
I'm not telling the truth</i>

82
00:03:38.285 --> 00:03:41.380
<i>I know. you know They
just don't have any proof</i>

83
00:03:41.455 --> 00:03:44.653
<i>Embrace the deception
Learn how to bend</i>

84
00:03:44.725 --> 00:03:48.685
<i>Your worst inhibitions tend
to psych you out in the end</i>

85
00:03:54.267 --> 00:03:56.702
You D-bags gonna
let me in or what?

86
00:03:57.170 --> 00:03:58.399
D-bags?

87
00:03:58.872 --> 00:04:00.704
Yeah. Come on in. Jim.

88
00:04:00.807 --> 00:04:01.934
(GRUNTS)

89
00:04:02.109 --> 00:04:03.133
(LAUGHS)

90
00:04:03.210 --> 00:04:04.610
Way not to be scared. flincher.

91
00:04:04.678 --> 00:04:07.170
I didn't flinch. You know
I have a caffeine tic.

92
00:04:07.247 --> 00:04:10.649
Look at this place.
Video games. lockers.

93
00:04:10.717 --> 00:04:12.276
You two haven't
grown up at all. huh?

94
00:04:12.352 --> 00:04:14.344
And you haven't grown up.

95
00:04:14.621 --> 00:04:15.680
Up.

96
00:04:16.823 --> 00:04:18.018
At all.

97
00:04:18.391 --> 00:04:22.351
Jimmy. as glad as we are to
see you. what are you doing here?

98
00:04:22.429 --> 00:04:24.398
What do you think I'm
doing here. barf beetle?

99
00:04:24.464 --> 00:04:27.298
I came to take your
lunch money. Hand it over!

100
00:04:27.367 --> 00:04:29.598
(LAUGHING)

101
00:04:29.669 --> 00:04:33.504
I'm just messing around.
Actually. I'm in town for work.

102
00:04:34.574 --> 00:04:36.270
I'm sensing...

103
00:04:36.343 --> 00:04:38.369
You became a jockey.

104
00:04:38.445 --> 00:04:39.606
A jockey?

105
00:04:39.679 --> 00:04:43.514
Yeah! One of the best jockeys.
Yeah. I won most of my races.

106
00:04:43.583 --> 00:04:45.609
Until the stupid Santa
Barbara meet started.

107
00:04:45.685 --> 00:04:47.654
Now I'm on some
ridiculous losing streak.

108
00:04:47.721 --> 00:04:49.899
Yeah. the last three favorites
I've ridden have all lost.

109
00:04:49.923 --> 00:04:51.516
And I know it wasn't
something I did.

110
00:04:51.591 --> 00:04:53.822
I've started to lose
all my best mounts.

111
00:04:53.894 --> 00:04:56.295
Mounts? Horses. Guster.

112
00:04:56.630 --> 00:04:57.825
What's wrong with you?

113
00:04:59.466 --> 00:05:02.959
Jimmy. what is it exactly
you'd like for us to do?

114
00:05:03.036 --> 00:05:07.303
Well. one of our friends from our old
school told me about your company.

115
00:05:07.374 --> 00:05:09.138
And even though it
sounds kind of gay.

116
00:05:09.209 --> 00:05:13.112
I thought I could hire you to
come down to the track and maybe

117
00:05:13.180 --> 00:05:15.513
psychically figure out
what's wrong with the horses.

118
00:05:15.582 --> 00:05:16.777
Okay. first of all.

119
00:05:16.850 --> 00:05:19.046
you ride on the back of
mounts while carrying a whip.

120
00:05:19.119 --> 00:05:21.486
That's much gayer
than what we do.

121
00:05:24.291 --> 00:05:26.936
Either way. we're busy right now.
so I don't think we'll be able to...

122
00:05:26.960 --> 00:05:28.656
We'll take the
case. I thought so.

123
00:05:28.728 --> 00:05:30.006
All right. Meet me
at the track at 2:00.

124
00:05:30.030 --> 00:05:31.521
And. as far as
anyone else knows.

125
00:05:31.598 --> 00:05:34.090
you guys are just some
really good old friends.

126
00:05:34.167 --> 00:05:36.295
Got it. dill holes?
(CHUCKLES) Got it.

127
00:05:36.369 --> 00:05:38.270
You can count on us dill holes.

128
00:05:38.338 --> 00:05:39.772
Goodbye. Jim.

129
00:05:41.041 --> 00:05:42.407
Are you crazy?

130
00:05:42.475 --> 00:05:44.171
I wouldn't say crazy.

131
00:05:44.244 --> 00:05:46.543
Maybe an eccentric
who looks good in jeans.

132
00:05:46.613 --> 00:05:51.074
Come on. Gus. You're not actually
still afraid of Jimmy Nickles. are you?

133
00:05:51.151 --> 00:05:53.677
We're not helping that little
monster. Shawn. Period.

134
00:05:53.753 --> 00:05:55.312
Okay. so Jimmy's still a jerk.

135
00:05:55.388 --> 00:05:59.587
We can see that. But the
truth is. I feel like I owe him.

136
00:05:59.659 --> 00:06:00.718
For what?

137
00:06:00.794 --> 00:06:03.730
If anything. he owes
us for 470 lunches.

138
00:06:03.797 --> 00:06:05.288
You know. I added that up once.

139
00:06:05.365 --> 00:06:07.994
And with inflation.
that's like $1.800.

140
00:06:08.068 --> 00:06:11.266
Look. do you remember when Jimmy got
kicked out of school in the fifth grade?

141
00:06:11.338 --> 00:06:12.362
For killing a teacher?

142
00:06:12.439 --> 00:06:15.136
For hitting Miss Lepky with a
spitball. She fell and got hurt.

143
00:06:15.208 --> 00:06:17.905
Same difference. She could've
very well have been killed.

144
00:06:17.978 --> 00:06:20.345
It was me who
ratted him out. Gus.

145
00:06:20.413 --> 00:06:21.904
You did that?

146
00:06:22.782 --> 00:06:24.011
Why didn't you ever tell me?

147
00:06:24.084 --> 00:06:27.885
You don't know all my secrets.
I'm a man of untold mysteries.

148
00:06:28.588 --> 00:06:32.116
If he found out. he'd come
back and gnaw off one of my toes.

149
00:06:32.192 --> 00:06:34.559
Ratting out Jimmy
Nickles? That's suicidal.

150
00:06:34.628 --> 00:06:35.891
I thought I saw him do it.

151
00:06:35.962 --> 00:06:38.908
and I told Principal Tropp because he
said he wasn't going to let the class go

152
00:06:38.932 --> 00:06:40.195
until somebody gave him a name.

153
00:06:40.267 --> 00:06:42.498
And what? You just
had to get home?

154
00:06:42.569 --> 00:06:46.665
Dude. <i>CHiPs</i> was gonna come on in. like.
20 minutes. What was I supposed to do?

155
00:06:46.740 --> 00:06:48.402
It was the one with
the freeway crash.

156
00:06:48.475 --> 00:06:52.276
Where the car used the empty car-carrier
trailer as a ramp and flipped in midair.

157
00:06:52.345 --> 00:06:53.973
That happens in
every episode. Shawn.

158
00:06:54.047 --> 00:06:55.777
I was under a lot of pressure.

159
00:07:19.406 --> 00:07:21.875
A. I always knew
you were a kiss-ass.

160
00:07:21.942 --> 00:07:24.741
And B. who cares? So
Jimmy got kicked out.

161
00:07:24.811 --> 00:07:26.302
It was the best day of my life.

162
00:07:26.379 --> 00:07:28.746
I could finally wear
underwear to school again.

163
00:07:28.815 --> 00:07:30.374
I don't know. Gus.

164
00:07:30.450 --> 00:07:32.476
I always sort of felt
like I got the wrong guy.

165
00:07:32.552 --> 00:07:34.096
I'll never forget the
look on Jimmy's face

166
00:07:34.120 --> 00:07:35.800
when they hauled him
out of class that day.

167
00:07:36.423 --> 00:07:39.791
I didn't do it! I
promise! I didn't do it!

168
00:07:41.194 --> 00:07:42.992
Look. after Jimmy got
kicked out of school.

169
00:07:43.063 --> 00:07:45.207
there were all these stories
about what happened to him.

170
00:07:45.231 --> 00:07:47.860
He ran away from home.
He got thrown in juvenile hall.

171
00:07:47.934 --> 00:07:50.904
Moved to a small town in Kansas
where they outlawed singing and dancing.

172
00:07:50.971 --> 00:07:53.236
That last one is <i>Footloose.</i>

173
00:07:53.306 --> 00:07:54.797
That's a coincidence.

174
00:07:54.874 --> 00:07:56.604
The point is. Jimmy's
life changed that day.

175
00:07:56.676 --> 00:07:58.542
and I feel like I gotta
make it up to him.

176
00:07:58.611 --> 00:08:00.589
Who knows. Gus? I might
have stunted the kid's growth.

177
00:08:00.613 --> 00:08:01.613
I don't know. Shawn.

178
00:08:01.681 --> 00:08:04.845
We're talking about the same dude who
made Aaron Rencher eat his own retainer.

179
00:08:04.918 --> 00:08:07.513
All right. how about this?
We take the case. right?

180
00:08:07.587 --> 00:08:09.681
We prove. for all the
Aaron Renchers of the world.

181
00:08:09.756 --> 00:08:12.487
we are no longer
afraid of Jimmy Nickles.

182
00:08:13.693 --> 00:08:14.786
All right. fine.

183
00:08:14.861 --> 00:08:18.423
But if we take this case. we're
going to overcharge him by $1.800.

184
00:08:18.498 --> 00:08:19.625
Done.

185
00:08:23.169 --> 00:08:27.470
(SHAWN NEIGHING)

186
00:08:29.809 --> 00:08:34.509
He doesn't like the oats. Or the alfalfa
pellets. They're too chewy for pellets.

187
00:08:34.581 --> 00:08:38.040
Pellets should be crunchy. They
should have a natural crunch to them.

188
00:08:38.818 --> 00:08:40.719
(SHAWN NEIGHING)

189
00:08:41.287 --> 00:08:42.983
(HORSE NEIGHING)

190
00:08:43.056 --> 00:08:47.118
Also. the donkey in stable
11 is a pathological liar.

191
00:08:47.193 --> 00:08:49.094
This is idiotic.

192
00:08:49.162 --> 00:08:52.360
Look. it takes a while for the
connection to take hold. Jimmy.

193
00:08:52.432 --> 00:08:54.924
Runny D and I are just
feeling each other out here.

194
00:08:55.001 --> 00:08:56.128
Whatever.

195
00:08:56.202 --> 00:08:58.501
I gotta go lose five pounds
before the next race.

196
00:08:58.571 --> 00:09:01.166
You got half an hour to
figure out what's going on.

197
00:09:04.010 --> 00:09:05.050
What'd you think. Runny D?

198
00:09:05.111 --> 00:09:06.739
I'll tell you what
he's thinking.

199
00:09:06.813 --> 00:09:09.248
He's thinking. "I hate Jimmy.

200
00:09:09.315 --> 00:09:13.616
"He pulled my shorts down in front
of Jenny Scarlatos in the cafeteria."

201
00:09:14.320 --> 00:09:15.515
(MIMICKING HORSE)

202
00:09:15.588 --> 00:09:17.989
You channeling the horse
or a little boy with a tight fade

203
00:09:18.058 --> 00:09:20.550
who used to wear his
OPs without a draw string?

204
00:09:20.627 --> 00:09:23.495
The horse. Shawn. I didn't have
a tight fade in the third grade.

205
00:09:23.563 --> 00:09:24.895
(WHISTLING)

206
00:09:26.032 --> 00:09:27.728
Hey! What's up?

207
00:09:28.401 --> 00:09:29.994
How are you?

208
00:09:33.673 --> 00:09:35.073
That's interesting.

209
00:09:37.210 --> 00:09:39.702
SHAWN: This place is weird
and borderline depressing.

210
00:09:39.779 --> 00:09:42.840
I mean. who are these people?
Who actually comes here?

211
00:09:42.916 --> 00:09:46.580
Well. well. well. This.
I never thought I'd see.

212
00:09:46.653 --> 00:09:48.622
Wow. Dad.

213
00:09:48.688 --> 00:09:51.783
Tell me you're wearing that shirt because
someone has to spot you from space.

214
00:09:51.858 --> 00:09:55.022
Very funny. Shawn. This happens
to be one of my lucky track shirts.

215
00:09:55.095 --> 00:09:56.095
I like it.

216
00:09:56.162 --> 00:09:58.631
I'd like it. too. if I had to
walk home in the dark.

217
00:09:58.698 --> 00:10:00.428
Henry. this your kid?

218
00:10:00.500 --> 00:10:03.129
Hey. kid. Phil "The
Thrill" Shershow.

219
00:10:03.203 --> 00:10:06.503
Shawn. This is Burton
"Oil Can" Guster.

220
00:10:06.573 --> 00:10:07.573
Good to meet you.

221
00:10:07.640 --> 00:10:11.543
Hey. Henry tell you for 20 years
I've been handicapping horses?

222
00:10:11.611 --> 00:10:13.773
That seems so very cruel.

223
00:10:14.481 --> 00:10:16.950
He must've told you I
hit the Pick Six in '87?

224
00:10:17.016 --> 00:10:19.884
Hey. Phil. it's pretty safe to
assume I haven't told him anything.

225
00:10:19.953 --> 00:10:21.785
Five minutes to post.
Gotta make a bet.

226
00:10:21.855 --> 00:10:25.314
Let me tell you. I like the
two-three-four trifecta box.

227
00:10:27.627 --> 00:10:30.893
I think your shirt and his shirt
should get together and go bowling.

228
00:10:30.964 --> 00:10:31.988
Ha-ha.

229
00:10:32.065 --> 00:10:34.043
You have all kinds of
interesting pals I don't know about.

230
00:10:34.067 --> 00:10:36.366
All right. Shawn. look.
Don't start. Phil is not a pal.

231
00:10:36.436 --> 00:10:38.314
He's a bad gambler who
doesn't know when to quit.

232
00:10:38.338 --> 00:10:40.534
But he also happens to
be on a hot streak right now.

233
00:10:40.607 --> 00:10:41.973
which is why I
let him talk to me.

234
00:10:42.041 --> 00:10:43.065
Not that I need it.

235
00:10:43.143 --> 00:10:46.307
I have won eight of 11
races today all by myself.

236
00:10:46.379 --> 00:10:47.403
(WHISTLES)

237
00:10:47.480 --> 00:10:48.991
All right. Shawn. what're
you doing out here anyway?

238
00:10:49.015 --> 00:10:50.950
I tried to drag you
out here for years.

239
00:10:51.017 --> 00:10:52.995
I'm only here today 'cause
we're working on a case.

240
00:10:53.019 --> 00:10:54.997
Well. you know. I think the
reason you never came out here

241
00:10:55.021 --> 00:10:57.461
is because to be a good
handicapper you gotta put in the time.

242
00:10:57.490 --> 00:11:01.052
You gotta do the research. You gotta study
the horses. You gotta study the jockeys.

243
00:11:01.127 --> 00:11:04.996
Something that takes patience
and follow through. which you lack.

244
00:11:05.064 --> 00:11:08.262
Yes. that and a shirt
from Mr. Furley's closet.

245
00:11:08.334 --> 00:11:09.700
(BELL RINGS)

246
00:11:09.769 --> 00:11:11.567
<i>BARRY: And the race is on!</i>

247
00:11:11.638 --> 00:11:13.607
<i>BabyFaced Assassin
takes the early lead.</i>

248
00:11:13.673 --> 00:11:16.268
<i>BabyFaced Assassin
strides into the first turn head.</i>

249
00:11:17.143 --> 00:11:18.634
So. what's the case?

250
00:11:18.711 --> 00:11:20.339
You ever heard of
a Jimmy Nickles?

251
00:11:20.413 --> 00:11:22.279
You mean Jimmy
Nicholas? Yeah. Solid jockey.

252
00:11:22.348 --> 00:11:24.078
Bad bet. He's
been losing lately.

253
00:11:24.150 --> 00:11:25.209
That's why he hired us.

254
00:11:25.285 --> 00:11:27.730
He thinks there may be something
psychically wrong with the horses.

255
00:11:27.754 --> 00:11:30.087
Yeah. The horses are losing.
that's what's wrong with them.

256
00:11:30.156 --> 00:11:31.647
Yeah. we didn't find anything.

257
00:11:31.724 --> 00:11:34.069
Of course you didn't. There's
a million reasons a horse loses.

258
00:11:34.093 --> 00:11:36.324
None of them have to do
with crystals and moonbeams.

259
00:11:36.396 --> 00:11:38.956
<i>BARRY: Youthful
Spirit is gaining.</i>

260
00:11:39.032 --> 00:11:40.762
<i>And it's Youthful Spirit!</i>

261
00:11:40.833 --> 00:11:42.699
<i>Youthful Spirit!</i>

262
00:11:44.704 --> 00:11:47.606
What I do is much more
than that. It's intuition.

263
00:11:47.707 --> 00:11:49.642
Son. you've got no case.

264
00:11:50.443 --> 00:11:53.242
Oh. well. thanks. We'll
just go home. then.

265
00:11:54.447 --> 00:11:55.506
WOMAN: Juan Carlos!

266
00:11:55.582 --> 00:11:57.141
MAN 1: Help him!

267
00:11:58.885 --> 00:12:00.877
<i>BARRY: Medical
assistance to the track.</i>

268
00:12:00.954 --> 00:12:03.947
<i>We need medical assistance to the
track immediately.</i> MAN 2: Jockey down!

269
00:12:04.023 --> 00:12:07.221
MAN 3: Juan Carlos! Carlos!

270
00:12:11.164 --> 00:12:16.262
So. a jockey who was alive at the
beginning of the race is dead by the end.

271
00:12:16.970 --> 00:12:20.429
Not to sound insensitive.
but I say we do have a case.

272
00:12:20.873 --> 00:12:22.171
That sounds insensitive.

273
00:12:22.242 --> 00:12:23.733
Yeah. I know.

274
00:12:28.047 --> 00:12:30.516
And you guys just
happened to be at the track?

275
00:12:30.583 --> 00:12:32.552
Jules. it's free churro day.

276
00:12:32.619 --> 00:12:34.144
Do they have a
cause of death yet?

277
00:12:34.220 --> 00:12:36.121
Probable heart attack.

278
00:12:43.463 --> 00:12:46.297
O'Hara. I need you to interview
the rest of those jockeys.

279
00:12:46.366 --> 00:12:47.698
(GROANING)

280
00:12:47.767 --> 00:12:48.826
What is that?

281
00:12:48.901 --> 00:12:52.030
Sorry. It's just little
people make me...

282
00:12:52.905 --> 00:12:55.636
Well. let's just say I had a bad
experience with a Christmas elf.

283
00:12:55.708 --> 00:12:57.677
What? He didn't give
you the right present?

284
00:12:57.744 --> 00:13:00.304
No. We dated.

285
00:13:00.380 --> 00:13:04.147
And then he dumped me for a
dancer from <i>The Ice Storm</i> on Ice.

286
00:13:05.918 --> 00:13:09.218
She is an enigma wrapped
in a little blonde riddle.

287
00:13:09.822 --> 00:13:13.884
Shawn. I don't think Juan
Carlos died of a heart attack.

288
00:13:13.960 --> 00:13:15.485
I only got to see
him for a second.

289
00:13:15.595 --> 00:13:17.427
but I'm pretty sure he
had bloodshot eyes.

290
00:13:17.497 --> 00:13:19.329
and his body was totally stiff.

291
00:13:19.399 --> 00:13:21.868
That's a reaction to a
tranquilizer or even a poison.

292
00:13:21.934 --> 00:13:23.926
Something affected
his nervous system.

293
00:13:24.003 --> 00:13:26.438
Thank you. Dr. Pratt.

294
00:13:26.506 --> 00:13:28.706
Let's see if we can get
another look at that body. Yeah.

295
00:13:28.775 --> 00:13:31.802
Hey. you two! Don't go anywhere!
I want to talk to you when I'm done.

296
00:13:31.878 --> 00:13:33.437
Gus has a cramp.

297
00:13:34.247 --> 00:13:35.772
I have a cramp?

298
00:13:36.983 --> 00:13:38.542
We have to pee.

299
00:13:39.319 --> 00:13:41.754
Fine. Just be back
in five minutes.

300
00:13:42.121 --> 00:13:43.866
We gotta pee? That's the
best you can come up with?

301
00:13:43.890 --> 00:13:45.415
Just hurry up.

302
00:13:47.327 --> 00:13:48.522
Really?

303
00:13:50.196 --> 00:13:52.927
How short was this
guy? Give it one more.

304
00:13:53.766 --> 00:13:55.098
We have boots.

305
00:13:55.535 --> 00:14:00.132
We've confirmed that a heart attack was
the cause of Juan Carlos Espinoza's death.

306
00:14:00.773 --> 00:14:02.674
Wait. Everyone. stop.

307
00:14:04.110 --> 00:14:07.638
Let's acknowledge that the
chief is wearing leopard print.

308
00:14:08.848 --> 00:14:10.316
And continue.

309
00:14:10.583 --> 00:14:11.881
I'm getting something.

310
00:14:11.951 --> 00:14:14.648
(STUTTERING)
A rose with a thorn!

311
00:14:14.721 --> 00:14:16.553
No. a rocket.

312
00:14:16.622 --> 00:14:18.614
Rikki Rocket. C.C. DeVille.

313
00:14:18.691 --> 00:14:20.057
David Lee Roth. Wrong band.

314
00:14:20.126 --> 00:14:21.321
Poison!

315
00:14:22.328 --> 00:14:24.194
Yes. Poison.

316
00:14:25.531 --> 00:14:28.023
Juan Carlos was poisoned.

317
00:14:28.101 --> 00:14:29.125
He's right.

318
00:14:29.202 --> 00:14:33.503
Chief. I am so sick of Lassiter
treating us like second-class citizens.

319
00:14:34.674 --> 00:14:36.802
What? You're right.

320
00:14:36.876 --> 00:14:39.004
Espinoza had a cocktail
of drugs in his system.

321
00:14:39.078 --> 00:14:42.038
Opiates. barbiturates. cocaine. three
different kinds of weight-loss drugs.

322
00:14:42.081 --> 00:14:43.549
Cialis and horse tranquilizers.

323
00:14:43.616 --> 00:14:44.709
Horse tranquilizers?

324
00:14:44.784 --> 00:14:46.650
Apparently. the guy
took everything in sight.

325
00:14:46.719 --> 00:14:48.931
He was four-foot-nine. and
three feet of that were drugs.

326
00:14:48.955 --> 00:14:51.083
And obviously his
heart couldn't handle it.

327
00:14:51.157 --> 00:14:53.456
A very thorough job. Detectives.

328
00:14:54.127 --> 00:14:55.561
I'm getting something else.

329
00:14:55.628 --> 00:14:58.530
<i>Juan Carlos was
having an affair!</i>

330
00:14:58.598 --> 00:15:00.191
With a married woman.

331
00:15:00.266 --> 00:15:01.734
Shawn. how do you know this?

332
00:15:01.801 --> 00:15:06.102
Same way that I know that as a child.
Lassy wanted nothing more than a pony.

333
00:15:08.274 --> 00:15:09.572
Oh. come on. who didn't?

334
00:15:09.642 --> 00:15:11.577
Anyone who wasn't
an 8-year-old girl?

335
00:15:11.644 --> 00:15:12.668
(EXCLAIMS)

336
00:15:12.745 --> 00:15:14.805
I see a tall blonde woman.

337
00:15:14.881 --> 00:15:16.349
Brigitte Nielsen? No.

338
00:15:16.416 --> 00:15:18.180
She has 23 diamonds
in her wedding ring.

339
00:15:18.251 --> 00:15:20.982
And she bandies about
the track this way and that.

340
00:15:21.053 --> 00:15:23.852
Shouldn't we at least find
this woman and talk to her?

341
00:15:23.923 --> 00:15:26.017
Do you know anything
about this. Detectives?

342
00:15:27.193 --> 00:15:31.722
Oh. Well. maybe you should find
out before we put this case to bed.

343
00:15:34.367 --> 00:15:37.895
Lassy. your childhood
must have been pure hell.

344
00:15:39.005 --> 00:15:41.804
The good news. I'm
available for hugs.

345
00:15:42.341 --> 00:15:43.341
(INHALES)

346
00:15:46.179 --> 00:15:47.977
Jules. how about it?

347
00:15:50.583 --> 00:15:52.142
Buddy. it's been a while.

348
00:15:52.218 --> 00:15:53.311
Please.

349
00:15:56.055 --> 00:16:00.390
(PANTING)

350
00:16:04.797 --> 00:16:05.797
You're here early.

351
00:16:05.865 --> 00:16:08.801
Yeah. Couldn't sleep. you know?

352
00:16:08.868 --> 00:16:12.635
Came in early. did a little
work on the case. went for a run.

353
00:16:12.705 --> 00:16:14.401
Oh. and I did this.

354
00:16:16.576 --> 00:16:18.841
Nice. I did some work as well.

355
00:16:18.911 --> 00:16:23.212
Turns out the horse tranquilizer Juan
Carlos had in his body was ketamine.

356
00:16:23.282 --> 00:16:27.310
which doesn't make any sense. 'cause
ketamine causes a state of anesthesia.

357
00:16:27.386 --> 00:16:30.481
Well. that's good. Gus. but I was
talking about the spitball incident.

358
00:16:30.556 --> 00:16:32.354
The spitball incident?

359
00:16:32.425 --> 00:16:33.916
Shawn. you need
to leave that alone.

360
00:16:33.993 --> 00:16:36.038
If you haven't figured it
out by now. you never will.

361
00:16:36.062 --> 00:16:37.894
I can't leave it alone. I won't.

362
00:16:37.964 --> 00:16:41.332
I've gone over it in my head a
thousand times. Just hear me out.

363
00:16:51.043 --> 00:16:52.477
What are you doing here?

364
00:16:52.545 --> 00:16:55.140
This is my head. dude. I
can do whatever I want.

365
00:16:55.214 --> 00:16:56.773
What'd we miss?
What's going on here?

366
00:16:56.849 --> 00:16:59.341
Is that what my hair
looks like in the future?

367
00:16:59.418 --> 00:17:00.852
It sure is.

368
00:17:00.920 --> 00:17:03.287
But I thought I'd be bald by 20.

369
00:17:04.090 --> 00:17:05.615
This changes everything.

370
00:17:05.691 --> 00:17:07.717
Yeah. it does. Think big.

371
00:17:07.793 --> 00:17:09.785
(EXCLAIMS)

372
00:17:10.830 --> 00:17:11.830
(LAUGHING)

373
00:17:12.298 --> 00:17:13.789
It was Jimmy!

374
00:17:17.270 --> 00:17:18.966
Whoa. whoa. whoa.

375
00:17:19.038 --> 00:17:22.338
He's sipping through the
straw. not spitting it out.

376
00:17:22.408 --> 00:17:24.434
It couldn't have been him.

377
00:17:26.779 --> 00:17:28.873
There was a second
spitter! Second spitter.

378
00:17:29.749 --> 00:17:31.411
That's so cool.

379
00:17:31.484 --> 00:17:34.477
Let it go. Shawn. Your
second spitter theory is crazy.

380
00:17:34.554 --> 00:17:36.234
Oh. yeah? What about
your <i>Teen Wolf</i> theory?

381
00:17:36.289 --> 00:17:37.655
Hey. that's just a fact.

382
00:17:37.723 --> 00:17:40.454
If any of us were in high school
and some dude became a wolf.

383
00:17:40.526 --> 00:17:43.071
we wouldn't be cool with him just
because he could dunk a basketball.

384
00:17:43.095 --> 00:17:46.135
I certainly wouldn't be selling "I
heart Wolf" T-shirts. I can tell you that.

385
00:17:46.198 --> 00:17:47.689
Save it for your podcast.

386
00:17:47.767 --> 00:17:49.201
Hey. you brought it up.

387
00:17:49.268 --> 00:17:51.965
I'm gonna go talk to Jimmy
Nickles. You look for TBW.

388
00:17:52.038 --> 00:17:53.904
TBW? Tall Blonde Woman.

389
00:17:53.973 --> 00:17:56.213
I abbreviated. Gus. All the
kids are doing it these days.

390
00:17:56.242 --> 00:17:57.266
Oh.

391
00:17:57.343 --> 00:17:58.420
Let's just hope we
don't run into my...

392
00:17:58.444 --> 00:18:00.174
YD? YD?

393
00:18:00.246 --> 00:18:01.805
Your Dad. And it's too late.

394
00:18:01.881 --> 00:18:04.680
Oh. my God. the
shirt has a brother!

395
00:18:05.184 --> 00:18:06.812
Very funny. Shawn.

396
00:18:07.086 --> 00:18:08.230
If you're looking
for your boy Jimmy.

397
00:18:08.254 --> 00:18:10.814
they just announced he was
taken off all the races for the day.

398
00:18:10.890 --> 00:18:12.859
Seriously? I wonder why.

399
00:18:12.925 --> 00:18:16.919
Isn't that Barry Saunder? The
announcer guy. He's like a local legend.

400
00:18:16.996 --> 00:18:18.862
Yeah. yeah. yeah
The Voice. right? Yeah.

401
00:18:18.931 --> 00:18:20.976
Hey. Dad. do you know him?
Can you introduce us or what?

402
00:18:21.000 --> 00:18:24.027
(STAMMERING) I met him once at a
policeman's ball. but it was years ago.

403
00:18:24.103 --> 00:18:25.594
Hey. Mr. Saunder!

404
00:18:25.671 --> 00:18:29.631
Hi. Look who's here! Your
old pal. Hank Spencer!

405
00:18:30.309 --> 00:18:31.368
Do I know you?

406
00:18:31.444 --> 00:18:34.380
No. but we know you.
What is it you always say?

407
00:18:34.447 --> 00:18:36.279
"And the race is on."
"And the race is on!"

408
00:18:36.349 --> 00:18:42.084
"And the race is on!"

409
00:18:42.154 --> 00:18:43.782
Hey. can you do
it for us one time?

410
00:18:43.856 --> 00:18:45.381
And the race is on.

411
00:18:45.458 --> 00:18:47.154
That's it right there.

412
00:18:47.226 --> 00:18:48.854
Why don't you
boys have a button.

413
00:18:48.928 --> 00:18:51.090
I'm sorry. Mr. Saunder.
I'm Henry Spencer.

414
00:18:51.163 --> 00:18:53.394
This is my son. Shawn.
and his friend Gus.

415
00:18:53.466 --> 00:18:55.110
They finally just started
coming to the races.

416
00:18:55.134 --> 00:18:56.534
Oh. Too bad.

417
00:18:56.836 --> 00:18:59.829
Track's probably closing
down after this meet.

418
00:19:00.373 --> 00:19:02.069
Twenty-five years
I've been doing this.

419
00:19:02.141 --> 00:19:03.370
Why's it closing down?

420
00:19:03.442 --> 00:19:05.104
Well. no one comes anymore.

421
00:19:05.177 --> 00:19:07.043
Is it because of his shirt?

422
00:19:07.113 --> 00:19:09.139
Sorry. Dad. this is
like a genocide of color.

423
00:19:09.215 --> 00:19:11.013
Somewhere a rainbow is weeping.

424
00:19:11.083 --> 00:19:15.544
Mr. Saunder. do you know why Jimmy Nickles
was pulled off all of his races today?

425
00:19:15.621 --> 00:19:17.487
We're his buddies. We
came down to see him.

426
00:19:17.556 --> 00:19:18.888
No.

427
00:19:18.958 --> 00:19:20.620
It's a shame. really.

428
00:19:20.693 --> 00:19:22.992
Jimmy was just getting
back to a full schedule.

429
00:19:23.062 --> 00:19:25.861
Juan Carlos had taken most of
his good mounts before he died.

430
00:19:25.931 --> 00:19:27.729
Really? We didn't know that.

431
00:19:27.800 --> 00:19:30.065
Oh. they quarreled
about it all the time.

432
00:19:30.136 --> 00:19:31.536
Did they?

433
00:19:31.604 --> 00:19:33.903
Shawn. look. TBW.

434
00:19:35.608 --> 00:19:37.668
Way to stay on the
abbreviation train. Gus.

435
00:19:37.743 --> 00:19:39.109
You mean the AT?

436
00:19:39.178 --> 00:19:42.307
Are you talking about
Janine? That's Jimmy's wife.

437
00:19:42.381 --> 00:19:43.474
Whoa. whoa. whoa. whoa.

438
00:19:46.552 --> 00:19:47.747
TBW is Jimmy's wife?

439
00:19:47.820 --> 00:19:48.820
Yes.

440
00:19:48.888 --> 00:19:52.450
Looks like Juan Carlos was
taking all of Jimmy's mounts.

441
00:19:56.262 --> 00:19:59.562
I didn't kill Juan Carlos!
I didn't do it. I swear!

442
00:19:59.899 --> 00:20:01.009
JIMMY: Come on! JANINE: Jimmy!

443
00:20:01.033 --> 00:20:02.865
JIMMY: You gotta
believe me! Back off!

444
00:20:02.968 --> 00:20:05.995
JANINE: Let me talk to him.
please! Come on. I didn't do it.

445
00:20:06.072 --> 00:20:08.007
GUS: Okay. so let
me get this straight.

446
00:20:08.074 --> 00:20:09.714
You took on this case
because you felt bad

447
00:20:09.742 --> 00:20:12.712
about Jimmy getting kicked out of
school for something he didn't do.

448
00:20:12.778 --> 00:20:15.179
And now you just convinced
the police to re-open a case

449
00:20:15.247 --> 00:20:18.115
that led to Jimmy being
arrested for murder.

450
00:20:19.118 --> 00:20:20.552
Did I ask for nutshelling?

451
00:20:22.254 --> 00:20:24.723
SHAWN: I think he looks
like a tangelo in that outfit.

452
00:20:24.790 --> 00:20:27.658
Or maybe a clementine
with seeds full of hate.

453
00:20:27.727 --> 00:20:29.787
I think he looks like
an evil little Creamsicle.

454
00:20:29.862 --> 00:20:32.331
(LAUGHS) You mean Dreamsicle.

455
00:20:32.398 --> 00:20:35.061
No. Shawn. Creamsicle.
They're exclusively orange.

456
00:20:35.134 --> 00:20:38.298
Okay. Lassiter says you can
have five minutes with Jimmy.

457
00:20:38.370 --> 00:20:39.497
Sweet.

458
00:20:39.572 --> 00:20:41.234
And good job. by the way.

459
00:20:41.307 --> 00:20:45.244
We never would have re-opened the
case and arrested him if it wasn't for you.

460
00:20:45.311 --> 00:20:47.280
You didn't tell
Jimmy that. did you?

461
00:20:47.346 --> 00:20:48.346
No.

462
00:20:48.414 --> 00:20:49.414
(SIGHS)

463
00:20:50.483 --> 00:20:51.883
I didn't kill Juan Carlos.

464
00:20:51.951 --> 00:20:52.951
We know.

465
00:20:53.052 --> 00:20:56.284
Someone must have tipped
them off. But I swear I didn't do it.

466
00:20:56.355 --> 00:21:00.417
Say. Jimmy. isn't that exactly
like you and the spitball incident?

467
00:21:04.029 --> 00:21:05.258
Guys!

468
00:21:06.132 --> 00:21:09.864
Look. I think what Gus is trying
to say is. we'd really like to help.

469
00:21:09.935 --> 00:21:12.404
We would. But the
evidence... What?

470
00:21:12.471 --> 00:21:14.269
Juan Carlos took all
your mounts. Yeah.

471
00:21:14.340 --> 00:21:15.706
You fought with
him over it. Yeah.

472
00:21:15.775 --> 00:21:17.819
They found ketamine in
your locker. That wasn't mine.

473
00:21:17.843 --> 00:21:20.278
And your wife was having
an affair with Juan Carlos.

474
00:21:20.346 --> 00:21:21.473
What?

475
00:21:23.716 --> 00:21:25.981
All right. Pervis. Put me down.

476
00:21:27.987 --> 00:21:29.319
Don't push me.

477
00:21:29.388 --> 00:21:31.266
I'm getting the feeling he
didn't know about the affair.

478
00:21:31.290 --> 00:21:32.314
You think?

479
00:21:32.391 --> 00:21:35.486
I'm sorry. I just... I can't
believe she would do that.

480
00:21:35.561 --> 00:21:39.931
Especially after I told her I wouldn't
sleep with any more Russian models.

481
00:21:42.067 --> 00:21:44.764
I think we may have
gotten off point. Jimmy.

482
00:21:44.837 --> 00:21:46.135
Let's go back to the beginning.

483
00:21:46.205 --> 00:21:50.404
Obviously the races you lost are
somehow connected to Juan Carlos's murder.

484
00:21:50.476 --> 00:21:52.076
So is there anything
else you can tell us

485
00:21:52.111 --> 00:21:55.081
or that you remember
about those races?

486
00:21:55.147 --> 00:21:57.082
No. The horses
were all running great.

487
00:21:57.149 --> 00:21:59.084
but right around
the clubhouse turn.

488
00:21:59.151 --> 00:22:01.518
they all faded down the stretch.

489
00:22:01.587 --> 00:22:03.988
All of them faded
down the stretch?

490
00:22:04.456 --> 00:22:06.584
You know what? Yeah.

491
00:22:07.359 --> 00:22:08.452
Good.

492
00:22:09.028 --> 00:22:11.190
That's a good place to begin.

493
00:22:14.300 --> 00:22:15.877
All right. that's enough.
Shawn. Let's go.

494
00:22:15.901 --> 00:22:18.302
You've been staring
at that thing for an hour.

495
00:22:18.370 --> 00:22:20.339
Let me take off my
shoes and try it lying down.

496
00:22:20.406 --> 00:22:24.070
No. Shawn. You don't have
anything. It's a dead end. Face it.

497
00:22:24.143 --> 00:22:25.503
We have to tell
Jimmy he's screwed.

498
00:22:25.544 --> 00:22:27.308
Fine. You tell Jimmy.

499
00:22:27.379 --> 00:22:30.838
Me? I never wanted to take
this case in the first place.

500
00:22:32.651 --> 00:22:33.675
I'll race you for it.

501
00:22:33.752 --> 00:22:35.687
What? No.

502
00:22:35.754 --> 00:22:36.847
That's right.

503
00:22:36.922 --> 00:22:38.754
And I know why. Why?

504
00:22:38.824 --> 00:22:41.236
Because I beat you in the 100-yard
dash in the Junior High Olympics.

505
00:22:41.260 --> 00:22:44.094
Please. First of all. you
know I had shin splints.

506
00:22:44.163 --> 00:22:46.189
a torn meniscus
and a plantar's wart.

507
00:22:46.265 --> 00:22:49.064
Gus. you copied those terms from
the glossary of our health textbook.

508
00:22:49.134 --> 00:22:50.278
You have no idea what they mean.

509
00:22:50.302 --> 00:22:51.361
Ask my doctor.

510
00:22:51.437 --> 00:22:54.965
I had a ruptured patella. too.
but I wasn't gonna say anything.

511
00:22:55.040 --> 00:22:56.440
Besides...

512
00:22:57.276 --> 00:22:59.711
Go! Oh. no! No. you didn't!

513
00:22:59.778 --> 00:23:02.976
(SHAWN EXCLAIMING)

514
00:23:05.017 --> 00:23:06.349
(CAMERA CLICKS)

515
00:23:08.654 --> 00:23:10.486
(BOTH PANTING)

516
00:23:15.494 --> 00:23:16.962
You almost had me.

517
00:23:17.029 --> 00:23:18.395
What?

518
00:23:18.464 --> 00:23:20.592
I had you by at least a foot.

519
00:23:21.467 --> 00:23:22.594
I'm gonna give this to you.

520
00:23:22.668 --> 00:23:23.727
I thought so.

521
00:23:23.802 --> 00:23:25.634
Not because you won.

522
00:23:25.704 --> 00:23:28.264
Because you need a victory in
your life more than I do right now.

523
00:23:28.307 --> 00:23:29.775
What?

524
00:23:29.842 --> 00:23:32.539
Oh. no. We're going again.

525
00:23:32.611 --> 00:23:34.341
I got a better idea.

526
00:23:36.215 --> 00:23:39.344
Seven flights of stairs just to
get another view of the track?

527
00:23:39.418 --> 00:23:41.649
Gus. this is the perfect
spot for us to see...

528
00:23:41.720 --> 00:23:43.780
You'll find...

529
00:23:43.856 --> 00:23:47.224
See where the magic
happens. I told you he'd be here.

530
00:23:47.559 --> 00:23:49.221
Can I help you fellas?

531
00:23:49.295 --> 00:23:50.991
Uh. yeah...

532
00:23:51.797 --> 00:23:53.163
And the race is on.

533
00:23:53.232 --> 00:23:54.461
(LAUGHS)

534
00:23:55.034 --> 00:23:56.711
I really don't think you
should be up here right now.

535
00:23:56.735 --> 00:23:59.175
I'm trying to finish my taped
announcements for the day. so...

536
00:23:59.238 --> 00:24:01.537
Ooh. can I do one? I've always
wanted to be an announcer.

537
00:24:01.607 --> 00:24:04.338
For the owner of a
red IROC-Z in lot 3.

538
00:24:04.410 --> 00:24:06.311
Kindly return your
comb to the back pocket

539
00:24:06.378 --> 00:24:09.780
of your acid-wash Z Cavariccis

540
00:24:09.848 --> 00:24:12.249
and turn off your headlights.

541
00:24:13.185 --> 00:24:14.813
What did you think of that. huh?

542
00:24:14.887 --> 00:24:16.253
Have a button.

543
00:24:16.322 --> 00:24:18.757
Hey. I've seen
one of these before.

544
00:24:19.391 --> 00:24:21.485
Yes. It's a shaman's staff.

545
00:24:21.560 --> 00:24:26.089
Yeah. I saw a special on the History
Channel about the Choctaw Indians.

546
00:24:26.165 --> 00:24:27.793
Oh. yes. The Cha-Ka Indians.

547
00:24:27.866 --> 00:24:30.859
Longstanding rivals of
the Sleestak cowboys.

548
00:24:30.936 --> 00:24:32.928
It's pronounced Cho-ko.

549
00:24:33.005 --> 00:24:35.702
Gave us the chocodile.
amongst other things.

550
00:24:35.774 --> 00:24:37.333
I don't think so.

551
00:24:37.409 --> 00:24:40.345
I've been collecting these
artifacts for a number of years.

552
00:24:40.412 --> 00:24:43.109
I'm actually one-sixteenth
Indian myself.

553
00:24:43.182 --> 00:24:44.912
But not Cherokee.

554
00:24:44.984 --> 00:24:47.681
Hey. Gus is one-sixteenth robot.

555
00:24:47.753 --> 00:24:51.190
And not the evil.
take-over-the-world from <i>I. Robot</i> kind.

556
00:24:53.292 --> 00:24:55.261
Oh. sorry.

557
00:24:56.128 --> 00:24:58.825
Hey! You're the guy that
tried to save Juan Carlos.

558
00:24:58.897 --> 00:25:00.832
Yeah. You were the
only one who tried to help.

559
00:25:00.899 --> 00:25:02.595
Way to go. You
should feel proud.

560
00:25:02.668 --> 00:25:03.692
Yeah.

561
00:25:03.769 --> 00:25:05.362
Uh. he died.

562
00:25:05.738 --> 00:25:07.468
Yes. he did do that.

563
00:25:11.710 --> 00:25:13.838
Well. gentlemen.

564
00:25:13.912 --> 00:25:17.280
Ryan and I have to go over some publicity
photos. so if you'd be kind enough...

565
00:25:17.349 --> 00:25:20.649
And the race is on!

566
00:25:21.854 --> 00:25:23.447
Cha-Ka? Really?

567
00:25:23.522 --> 00:25:25.115
Yeah. I'd be
embarrassed if I were you.

568
00:25:25.190 --> 00:25:26.522
I'm not embarrassed at all. Gus.

569
00:25:26.592 --> 00:25:29.721
A <i>Land of the Lost</i> reference is virtually
unheard of in everyday conversation.

570
00:25:29.795 --> 00:25:30.922
Can we go and see Jimmy now?

571
00:25:30.996 --> 00:25:32.123
Not yet.

572
00:25:32.197 --> 00:25:33.927
Barry has tapes of
the races in there.

573
00:25:33.999 --> 00:25:36.111
which means there's a copy
of the one Juan Carlos died in.

574
00:25:36.135 --> 00:25:39.196
I don't know why I didn't think of
this before. We need to see that tape.

575
00:25:39.271 --> 00:25:41.182
There's no way Barry's
gonna let us back in there.

576
00:25:41.206 --> 00:25:42.550
Don't the police
have a copy of it?

577
00:25:42.574 --> 00:25:45.942
They do. but Lassiter's convinced
the case is closed. so he won't help.

578
00:25:46.011 --> 00:25:48.606
Which means I'm gonna have to
do something I know I will regret.

579
00:25:48.680 --> 00:25:51.115
What. ride your dirt bike off
of David King's roof again?

580
00:25:51.183 --> 00:25:52.583
No.

581
00:25:52.651 --> 00:25:54.552
Ask my dad for a favor.

582
00:25:56.822 --> 00:25:59.986
So I was hoping that in your
very meticulous detail mode.

583
00:26:00.059 --> 00:26:02.051
it occurred to you to...

584
00:26:05.631 --> 00:26:07.122
I can't do it.

585
00:26:07.900 --> 00:26:09.994
He wants to know if you
tape all the horse races.

586
00:26:10.069 --> 00:26:11.469
Of course I do. Awesome.

587
00:26:11.537 --> 00:26:13.506
Can we watch the one
when Juan Carlos died?

588
00:26:13.572 --> 00:26:16.371
You may. On one condition.

589
00:26:21.413 --> 00:26:25.509
The deal is you go with me to
the Derby on Sunday in that shirt.

590
00:26:26.585 --> 00:26:29.453
What did I say about
regret. Gus? What did I say?

591
00:26:29.521 --> 00:26:31.717
I think you pull it off. Shawn.

592
00:26:33.525 --> 00:26:34.891
Fine.

593
00:26:34.960 --> 00:26:36.258
All right. here's the race.

594
00:26:36.328 --> 00:26:37.768
Juan Carlos is on
the number 8 horse.

595
00:26:37.830 --> 00:26:40.459
I remember this 'cause Phil
convinced me to go with the long shot.

596
00:26:40.532 --> 00:26:43.696
The one time I go with
the guy and the horse loses.

597
00:26:45.437 --> 00:26:47.906
I don't get it. What are we
missing? What aren't we seeing?

598
00:26:47.973 --> 00:26:50.499
Maybe nothing. Maybe
Jimmy did poison Juan Carlos.

599
00:26:50.576 --> 00:26:51.976
I know he didn't
poison Juan Carlos.

600
00:26:52.044 --> 00:26:53.655
Just like I know
there's a second spitter.

601
00:26:53.679 --> 00:26:57.116
Shawn. once again. you're focusing too
much attention on one aspect of the case.

602
00:26:57.182 --> 00:26:58.182
Close your eyes.

603
00:26:58.250 --> 00:27:00.261
No. I'm not jumping through
anymore of your hoops today.

604
00:27:00.285 --> 00:27:01.596
You need to broaden
your vision. Shawn.

605
00:27:01.620 --> 00:27:04.021
You need to look at
the outskirts of the case.

606
00:27:04.089 --> 00:27:06.854
What does that even
mean? "Broaden my vision?

607
00:27:06.925 --> 00:27:09.918
"Look at the outskirts of a..."
You know what. I am out of here.

608
00:27:09.995 --> 00:27:13.693
No. no. no. Not today.
You sound like Oprah.

609
00:27:13.765 --> 00:27:17.202
I don't even know why I bother coming
here. It's a complete waste of time!

610
00:27:20.005 --> 00:27:21.098
(DOOR OPENING)

611
00:27:22.407 --> 00:27:26.367
A little girl outside just started
crying when she saw this shirt.

612
00:27:32.417 --> 00:27:33.851
Oh. good. good. You're here.

613
00:27:33.919 --> 00:27:35.930
You texted me seven times.
Said it was an emergency.

614
00:27:35.954 --> 00:27:38.389
Yes. a color emergency.
But I think I figured it out.

615
00:27:38.457 --> 00:27:43.191
The walls were sandbar white to suppress
all creative thought and hide the asbestos.

616
00:27:43.262 --> 00:27:44.753
The walls of what?

617
00:27:44.830 --> 00:27:46.560
Miss Lepky's classroom.

618
00:27:46.632 --> 00:27:48.999
Why is my name
on the detention list?

619
00:27:49.067 --> 00:27:51.764
You got caught eating a
Kit Kat out of the trashcan.

620
00:27:51.837 --> 00:27:53.533
The point is. when
I left my dad's...

621
00:27:53.605 --> 00:27:55.767
You mean stormed
out like a little girl?

622
00:27:55.841 --> 00:27:57.207
I did not.

623
00:27:58.076 --> 00:28:00.443
I did. I'll give you that.

624
00:28:01.246 --> 00:28:03.147
I realized my dad
was actually right.

625
00:28:03.215 --> 00:28:05.446
I needed to broaden my vision.

626
00:28:05.517 --> 00:28:09.511
And that's when I remembered. We
all switched seats in class that week.

627
00:28:09.588 --> 00:28:12.854
Right. I had to sit behind Janie
Dorn and her creepy neck hair.

628
00:28:12.925 --> 00:28:17.590
And Jimmy moved over two rows.

629
00:28:17.663 --> 00:28:20.997
Meaning that the second
spitter was on the other side.

630
00:28:22.734 --> 00:28:24.259
Gus. get him.

631
00:28:24.336 --> 00:28:26.567
Shawn. what does this
have to do with horse racing?

632
00:28:27.139 --> 00:28:28.339
I haven't gotten that far yet.

633
00:28:28.407 --> 00:28:30.308
Let me know when
you figure it out.

634
00:28:34.379 --> 00:28:35.904
Let go. Jimmy.

635
00:28:39.451 --> 00:28:40.451
(CELL PHONE RINGING)

636
00:28:40.652 --> 00:28:42.644
Hello? <i>SHAWN:
Dude. I figured it out.</i>

637
00:28:43.655 --> 00:28:45.123
Was that really necessary?

638
00:28:45.190 --> 00:28:47.352
No. but it was dope.

639
00:28:50.195 --> 00:28:52.607
<i>BARRY: BabyFaced Assassin
strides into the first turn at the head</i>

640
00:28:52.631 --> 00:28:55.396
<i>with None Other right on its
tail. BabyFaced Assassin...</i>

641
00:28:55.467 --> 00:28:56.867
Wait for it.

642
00:28:56.969 --> 00:28:59.849
<i>With None Other trade the top spot
as they race around the second turn.</i>

643
00:29:00.339 --> 00:29:01.432
Right there!

644
00:29:01.506 --> 00:29:04.442
The clubhouse turn. Juan
Carlos gets hit by something.

645
00:29:04.509 --> 00:29:06.487
This was just like the
spitball incident with Jimmy.

646
00:29:06.511 --> 00:29:09.140
I was so focused on the stretch
that I never looked anywhere else.

647
00:29:09.214 --> 00:29:12.082
You know. I didn't
broaden my vision. Dad.

648
00:29:12.150 --> 00:29:14.095
Shawn. I'd love nothing
more than to tell you I'm right.

649
00:29:14.119 --> 00:29:15.530
but I have no idea
what I'm right about.

650
00:29:15.554 --> 00:29:19.116
The question is why would
somebody kill someone like that?

651
00:29:24.896 --> 00:29:27.661
Guys! Juan Carlos's
death was an accident.

652
00:29:27.733 --> 00:29:30.066
Yeah! Whatever hit him
was meant for a horse.

653
00:29:30.135 --> 00:29:33.731
This isn't about murder.
It's about fixing races.

654
00:29:41.013 --> 00:29:42.311
Are the tapes ready? Check.

655
00:29:42.381 --> 00:29:43.747
Fake psychic
ability? Full of it.

656
00:29:43.815 --> 00:29:45.283
Yes. you are.

657
00:29:48.353 --> 00:29:50.151
Mr. Spencer. what is going on?

658
00:29:50.222 --> 00:29:52.657
First you help us get... Oh.

659
00:29:52.724 --> 00:29:55.250
Get Jimmy Nicholas. Now
you claim he's innocent?

660
00:29:55.327 --> 00:29:59.162
I'm sorry. Chief. Psychic solar
flares have temporarily blinded me.

661
00:29:59.231 --> 00:30:02.633
My sense of smell has
compensated for my lack of sight.

662
00:30:03.635 --> 00:30:05.604
Lilacs in a meadow.

663
00:30:08.006 --> 00:30:09.975
Is that Camay?
Oh. this is ridiculous.

664
00:30:10.042 --> 00:30:12.011
We've got big boy
police work to do.

665
00:30:12.077 --> 00:30:14.876
Wait. My eyes are
starting to adjust.

666
00:30:14.946 --> 00:30:17.040
Where are we?

667
00:30:17.115 --> 00:30:19.084
We're in the video room!

668
00:30:20.585 --> 00:30:22.417
I'm blind. Gus. Not deaf.

669
00:30:22.487 --> 00:30:26.049
Mr. Spencer. we don't have
time for this. If you wanted to...

670
00:30:27.326 --> 00:30:29.693
Those tapes! What
are on those tapes?

671
00:30:29.761 --> 00:30:31.041
They're the tapes
from the track.

672
00:30:31.096 --> 00:30:33.031
We reviewed them. but
we didn't find anything.

673
00:30:33.098 --> 00:30:37.559
Six-twenty.
Six-twenty-eight. Seven-two.

674
00:30:38.236 --> 00:30:40.796
Doritos. Big Gulp. Slurpee.

675
00:30:40.872 --> 00:30:42.340
7-Eleven?

676
00:30:42.941 --> 00:30:45.206
These are all the
dates on the tapes.

677
00:30:45.277 --> 00:30:47.678
Gus. let's play these tapes.

678
00:30:52.984 --> 00:30:54.111
Stop.

679
00:30:56.521 --> 00:30:57.648
SHAWN: Stop.

680
00:31:00.325 --> 00:31:01.384
Stop.

681
00:31:06.131 --> 00:31:07.224
Stop!

682
00:31:08.266 --> 00:31:11.361
These are Jimmy's races. This
one is when Juan Carlos died.

683
00:31:11.436 --> 00:31:13.337
That must be why
they're in my head.

684
00:31:13.405 --> 00:31:17.308
All of these horses faded down the
stretch. as if affected by something.

685
00:31:17.376 --> 00:31:19.140
And look. Here.

686
00:31:19.211 --> 00:31:22.648
Juan Carlos is clearly hit by
something at the clubhouse turn.

687
00:31:22.714 --> 00:31:26.082
He felt the effects immediately
because he's a tiny human person.

688
00:31:26.151 --> 00:31:28.848
With the horses. it takes
longer for them to feel the effects.

689
00:31:28.920 --> 00:31:30.252
And your point is?

690
00:31:30.322 --> 00:31:33.781
Whatever hit Juan Carlos
was intended for his horse.

691
00:31:34.826 --> 00:31:36.954
What I'm saying is that
this was an accident.

692
00:31:37.028 --> 00:31:40.726
Mr. Spencer. that's a very interesting
theory. but it's all circumstantial.

693
00:31:40.799 --> 00:31:42.427
We're gonna need
some hard evidence.

694
00:31:42.501 --> 00:31:44.868
Yeah. but thanks
for the AV class.

695
00:31:44.936 --> 00:31:48.202
<i>Youthful Spirit fades down the
stretch. No. wait. he's gaining.</i>

696
00:31:48.273 --> 00:31:51.539
<i>It's Youthful Spirit!
Youthful Spirit pulls it out!</i>

697
00:31:53.879 --> 00:31:57.179
<i>Youthful Spirit fades down the
stretch. No. wait. he's gaining.</i>

698
00:31:57.249 --> 00:31:59.081
<i>It's Youthful
Spirit. pulls it out!</i>

699
00:31:59.151 --> 00:32:01.711
The announcer!
It's the announcer!

700
00:32:02.354 --> 00:32:05.518
He sounds surprised.
nay. shocked.

701
00:32:05.590 --> 00:32:08.719
when Youthful Spirit
doesn't fade down the stretch.

702
00:32:08.794 --> 00:32:09.955
Listen.

703
00:32:10.028 --> 00:32:13.328
<i>Youthful Spirit fades down the
stretch. No. wait. he's gaining.</i>

704
00:32:13.398 --> 00:32:16.664
<i>It's Youthful Spirit.
Youthful Spirit pulls it out!</i>

705
00:32:17.402 --> 00:32:20.882
He was expecting something to happen to Juan
Carlos's horse. That means he's a part of it.

706
00:32:20.906 --> 00:32:22.550
Chief. every psychic
nerve in my body tells me

707
00:32:22.574 --> 00:32:24.619
that something really big is going
to happen at the Derby tomorrow

708
00:32:24.643 --> 00:32:26.976
and that we all
need to be there.

709
00:32:28.680 --> 00:32:30.842
All right. It's too late
to cancel the races.

710
00:32:30.916 --> 00:32:34.080
but I can approve a police
presence at the track.

711
00:32:34.286 --> 00:32:39.224
(INDISTINCT CHATTERING)

712
00:32:39.291 --> 00:32:43.126
I've never been in the jockey club before.
Shawn. Thanks for getting me in here.

713
00:32:43.195 --> 00:32:45.426
It's a good thing we
wore our lucky shirts. huh?

714
00:32:45.497 --> 00:32:47.523
Yeah. I'm just worried
someone's gonna

715
00:32:47.599 --> 00:32:50.763
stare directly at the
pattern and have a seizure.

716
00:32:50.836 --> 00:32:53.738
(BUGLE BLOWING)

717
00:32:53.805 --> 00:32:56.798
Shawn. we've had people
watching Barry for the last six races

718
00:32:56.875 --> 00:32:58.875
and they haven't seen
anything out of the ordinary.

719
00:32:58.910 --> 00:33:01.209
Admit it. You
guys don't have it.

720
00:33:02.280 --> 00:33:04.215
Don't worry. we have it.

721
00:33:04.282 --> 00:33:05.359
I don't know if we have it.

722
00:33:05.383 --> 00:33:07.818
We just gotta figure
out how it all connects.

723
00:33:07.886 --> 00:33:10.231
So what does this Indian stuff I
got off the Internet connect to?

724
00:33:10.255 --> 00:33:13.020
That's what we in the fake
psychic community call a hunch.

725
00:33:13.091 --> 00:33:14.457
<i>BARRY: Ladies and gentlemen.</i>

726
00:33:14.526 --> 00:33:16.392
<i>the horses have
reached the starting gate</i>

727
00:33:16.461 --> 00:33:18.930
<i>for the 84th running of
the Santa Barbara Derby.</i>

728
00:33:18.997 --> 00:33:20.124
WOMAN: Yes! Yes!

729
00:33:20.198 --> 00:33:22.531
(BELL RINGS)

730
00:33:22.601 --> 00:33:23.728
<i>And the race is on!</i>

731
00:33:23.802 --> 00:33:26.169
<i>Uh-oh! Two horses bump
as they come out of the gate!</i>

732
00:33:26.238 --> 00:33:29.037
<i>It's the 3 horse. Scare The
Prize. and the 4. Biased Opinion.</i>

733
00:33:29.107 --> 00:33:32.509
<i>Kate's Conscience takes the early
lead as the horses reach the first turn.</i>

734
00:33:32.577 --> 00:33:35.775
<i>Authority Figure makes a strong
move on the inside of Owner's Caprice</i>

735
00:33:35.847 --> 00:33:38.248
<i>down the backstretch. Authority
Figure and Kate's Conscience</i>

736
00:33:38.316 --> 00:33:39.841
<i>battle their way
past the fall turn.</i>

737
00:33:39.918 --> 00:33:42.649
<i>Authority Figure
begins to take control.</i>

738
00:34:00.805 --> 00:34:03.866
Phil is not a pal. He's a bad gambler
who doesn't know when to quit.

739
00:34:03.942 --> 00:34:05.911
But he also happens
to be on a hot streak.

740
00:34:05.977 --> 00:34:10.073
Henry tell you I like the
two-three-four trifecta box? Huh?

741
00:34:10.148 --> 00:34:13.141
Track's probably closing
down after this meet.

742
00:34:13.718 --> 00:34:16.278
Twenty-five years
I've been doing this.

743
00:34:16.555 --> 00:34:18.115
<i>BARRY: Authority
Figure is almost there.</i>

744
00:34:18.156 --> 00:34:20.853
Dude. I got it. Get
everyone down to the track.

745
00:34:20.926 --> 00:34:23.293
<i>Authority Figure wins with ease!</i>

746
00:34:25.263 --> 00:34:28.392
Guys. I really would like
to cash in my tickets now.

747
00:34:28.466 --> 00:34:30.511
Well. how did she feel
coming around the backstretch?

748
00:34:30.535 --> 00:34:32.527
Everybody hold your horses!

749
00:34:32.604 --> 00:34:33.604
(HORSE NEIGHS)

750
00:34:35.006 --> 00:34:37.999
I meant metaphorically.
but I like the love.

751
00:34:38.076 --> 00:34:39.669
I sensed a plan.

752
00:34:39.978 --> 00:34:41.970
Hatched from the desperation
of watching the track

753
00:34:42.047 --> 00:34:44.744
they all loved so
much shuttered forever.

754
00:34:44.816 --> 00:34:47.843
Isn't that right. Barry?

755
00:34:47.919 --> 00:34:51.913
Excuse me? You
are so not excused.

756
00:34:51.990 --> 00:34:53.701
You see. the track is
closing down this year.

757
00:34:53.725 --> 00:34:57.287
and Barry finally figured
out a way to get paid.

758
00:34:57.362 --> 00:35:00.332
But it was the equine
who told me he had help.

759
00:35:01.600 --> 00:35:03.865
Two people with intimate
knowledge of the races

760
00:35:03.935 --> 00:35:05.767
<i>and access to the entire track.</i>

761
00:35:05.837 --> 00:35:08.204
<i>They figured out how to
control the outcome of the races</i>

762
00:35:08.273 --> 00:35:10.742
<i>by getting rid of the favorites.</i>

763
00:35:10.809 --> 00:35:13.421
And because there were only a
few horses in the race to begin with.

764
00:35:13.445 --> 00:35:17.246
they bet on the rest of the field. and
their odds of winning went way up.

765
00:35:17.315 --> 00:35:20.046
That is insane. We
didn't do anything.

766
00:35:20.118 --> 00:35:23.316
That's not entirely true. Whoa.
whoa. what's happening here?

767
00:35:23.388 --> 00:35:24.388
Gus. little help. buddy.

768
00:35:24.456 --> 00:35:25.549
I don't do horses. Shawn.

769
00:35:25.624 --> 00:35:27.957
Dale! Dale.

770
00:35:28.860 --> 00:35:30.522
Hold that thought.

771
00:35:37.102 --> 00:35:38.126
What was I saying?

772
00:35:38.203 --> 00:35:39.831
Barry was saying
they didn't do anything.

773
00:35:39.938 --> 00:35:40.962
No.

774
00:35:41.039 --> 00:35:42.473
Really?

775
00:35:42.540 --> 00:35:44.873
He used Phil to make all
the bets on the long shots.

776
00:35:44.943 --> 00:35:49.176
And Ryan here. well. he took
care of knocking out the favorites

777
00:35:49.247 --> 00:35:51.045
from his perch in
the camera well.

778
00:35:51.116 --> 00:35:52.311
With what? His camera?

779
00:35:52.384 --> 00:35:53.443
Exactly.

780
00:35:53.518 --> 00:35:56.784
Lassy. do me a favor. Take
that camera off Ryan's neck.

781
00:35:56.855 --> 00:35:58.414
Give it a look.

782
00:36:02.560 --> 00:36:05.496
There's no lens. It's some
kind of firing mechanism.

783
00:36:05.563 --> 00:36:08.692
Which is why he didn't follow
the horses down the track.

784
00:36:08.767 --> 00:36:11.362
I just wanted to make some
money. It was Barry's idea.

785
00:36:11.436 --> 00:36:14.099
Shut up. Ryan! They
can't prove anything.

786
00:36:14.172 --> 00:36:16.573
I'm getting
something. A fraction.

787
00:36:16.941 --> 00:36:19.103
One-fifth. one-tenth.

788
00:36:20.645 --> 00:36:22.170
one-sixteenth.

789
00:36:22.547 --> 00:36:24.539
Barry's one-sixteenth
Choctaw Indian! Oh. no.

790
00:36:24.616 --> 00:36:27.950
And what are the Choctaw Indians
known for? Besides chocodiles.

791
00:36:28.019 --> 00:36:31.922
For using blowguns to kill
animals with darts dipped in poison.

792
00:36:32.590 --> 00:36:35.890
Gus shoots and scores.
with an assist from Wikipedia.

793
00:36:36.394 --> 00:36:38.727
<i>SHAWN: They used
darts dipped in ketamine.</i>

794
00:36:38.797 --> 00:36:40.959
<i>a horse tranquilizer strong
enough to slow down a horse</i>

795
00:36:41.032 --> 00:36:42.056
<i>in the middle of a race.</i>

796
00:36:42.133 --> 00:36:45.126
With darts small enough to be
missed on a thousand-pound horse.

797
00:36:45.203 --> 00:36:46.933
But the problem was.

798
00:36:47.005 --> 00:36:49.338
<i>they accidentally
shot Juan Carlos.</i>

799
00:36:49.407 --> 00:36:52.400
The ketamine. mixed with all
the other drugs in his system

800
00:36:52.477 --> 00:36:55.379
and the adrenaline
from the race killed him.

801
00:36:58.850 --> 00:37:01.843
Ryan. you weren't trying
to save Juan Carlos's life.

802
00:37:01.920 --> 00:37:04.287
<i>You were looking
for the evidence.</i>

803
00:37:08.326 --> 00:37:11.956
And they almost pulled it
off by framing poor Jimmy.

804
00:37:12.030 --> 00:37:15.797
<i>but they couldn't resist one
more big payday at today's race.</i>

805
00:37:19.003 --> 00:37:23.532
It's like my dad always says.
"Real men take bubble baths.

806
00:37:24.642 --> 00:37:27.578
"and a bad gambler
never knows when to quit."

807
00:37:27.979 --> 00:37:29.845
Not bad. kid. Not bad.

808
00:37:30.381 --> 00:37:32.612
Let's go. Get them out of here.

809
00:37:33.384 --> 00:37:36.821
Now. who wants to take a picture
with the winning horse and jockey?

810
00:37:36.888 --> 00:37:38.857
Come on. Dad! Gus.
get over here. Hey.

811
00:37:38.923 --> 00:37:41.893
I finally get my picture
with us in our track shirts.

812
00:37:41.960 --> 00:37:44.452
Memories. Shawn.
That's what it's all about.

813
00:37:44.529 --> 00:37:46.430
Just act natural. Yeah.

814
00:37:51.236 --> 00:37:53.467
Guys. I don't know what to say.

815
00:37:53.538 --> 00:37:57.236
I guess you're not such total
fart knockers after all. Thanks.

816
00:37:57.308 --> 00:37:59.709
That's so sweet.

817
00:38:00.779 --> 00:38:04.443
Gus. isn't there something you
wanted to say to Jimmy here?

818
00:38:08.987 --> 00:38:10.546
Yes. I do.

819
00:38:10.622 --> 00:38:12.266
I've been wanting to
say this for a long time.

820
00:38:12.290 --> 00:38:15.419
You know. back in school...
You know what? About that.

821
00:38:15.493 --> 00:38:17.257
I had some time to
think while I was in jail.

822
00:38:17.328 --> 00:38:20.162
and maybe I didn't treat
you guys so good back then.

823
00:38:20.231 --> 00:38:21.995
Especially you. Guster.

824
00:38:22.066 --> 00:38:25.503
So. I'm sorry. I'm sorry for
giving you wedgies. swirlies.

825
00:38:25.570 --> 00:38:28.369
Jimmy Nickle sandwiches.
stuffing you in the trashcan

826
00:38:28.439 --> 00:38:31.637
and putting boogers
in your clarinet case.

827
00:38:31.709 --> 00:38:34.008
(CHUCKLES) Whoa!

828
00:38:34.078 --> 00:38:37.515
Feels good to get that off
my chest after all these years.

829
00:38:37.582 --> 00:38:39.448
Yeah. I can imagine.

830
00:38:40.485 --> 00:38:44.354
Say. Shawn. Isn't there something
you wanna get off of your chest?

831
00:38:45.857 --> 00:38:46.901
Are you gonna
tell him if I don't?

832
00:38:46.925 --> 00:38:48.553
What do you think?

833
00:38:48.726 --> 00:38:49.726
(SIGHS)

834
00:38:50.395 --> 00:38:52.830
All right. Jimmy.
here's the thing.

835
00:38:53.131 --> 00:38:56.101
I'm the one that ratted you
out over the spitball incident.

836
00:38:56.167 --> 00:38:58.295
Okay? I'm the one that
got you kicked out of school.

837
00:38:58.369 --> 00:39:01.032
And I'm the one that you should
blame for almost ruining your life.

838
00:39:01.105 --> 00:39:02.437
It was me.

839
00:39:06.211 --> 00:39:08.112
Almost ruining my life?

840
00:39:08.179 --> 00:39:09.909
Hey. I went to live
with my dad in Maui.

841
00:39:09.981 --> 00:39:11.449
He let me do anything I wanted.

842
00:39:11.516 --> 00:39:13.747
I ate pizza and cookie
dough for breakfast.

843
00:39:13.818 --> 00:39:15.150
I had a racecar bed.

844
00:39:15.220 --> 00:39:16.813
I lost my virginity at 13.

845
00:39:16.888 --> 00:39:18.799
It was the greatest thing
that ever happened to me.

846
00:39:18.823 --> 00:39:20.223
(HORN BLOWS)

847
00:39:21.192 --> 00:39:22.285
Hi!

848
00:39:23.361 --> 00:39:26.388
Oh. You two are
back together. huh?

849
00:39:26.464 --> 00:39:29.229
Dude. she's a former Miss Oxnard

850
00:39:29.300 --> 00:39:32.429
with no sense of smell
and her dad owns an airport.

851
00:39:32.503 --> 00:39:35.496
Of course we're back
together. Later-o. boys.

852
00:39:45.283 --> 00:39:49.584
Okay. see. that right there
makes total sense in the world.

853
00:39:49.654 --> 00:39:52.180
Yeah. but we can feel
good about solving the case.

854
00:39:52.257 --> 00:39:53.350
Ehh.

855
00:39:53.958 --> 00:39:56.120
Don't you "ehh" me.

856
00:39:56.194 --> 00:39:58.925
Dude. I broke up a highly
intricate race-fixing syndicate

857
00:39:58.997 --> 00:40:00.795
while wearing a shirt
designed by a monkey

858
00:40:00.865 --> 00:40:02.176
coming off a
three-day sugar binge.

859
00:40:02.200 --> 00:40:03.566
Yes. yes. you did. Shawn.

860
00:40:03.635 --> 00:40:04.678
But you still
haven't figured out

861
00:40:04.702 --> 00:40:07.297
who the second spitter
was in Miss Lepky's class.

862
00:40:08.640 --> 00:40:09.640
(CHUCKLES)

863
00:40:12.210 --> 00:40:13.678
Gus? Yes?

864
00:40:15.013 --> 00:40:16.379
You didn't.

865
00:40:16.848 --> 00:40:18.180
Yes. I did.

866
00:40:21.085 --> 00:40:23.054
(EXCLAIMS)

867
00:40:23.655 --> 00:40:24.655
(LAUGHING)

868
00:40:35.099 --> 00:40:36.567
You did that?

869
00:40:37.135 --> 00:40:38.312
And you never told me about it?

870
00:40:38.336 --> 00:40:40.100
You don't know all
my secrets. Shawn.

871
00:40:40.171 --> 00:40:43.437
I guess I. too. am a
man of untold mysteries.

872
00:40:43.508 --> 00:40:46.342
Burton Guster. I'm seeing you
in a completely different light.

873
00:40:46.411 --> 00:40:49.939
You are. dare I say. dastardly.

874
00:40:50.014 --> 00:40:52.381
Hey. I didn't want Miss
Lepky to get hurt or anything.

875
00:40:52.450 --> 00:40:54.715
but when Jimmy got
blamed. my mouth was shut.

876
00:40:54.786 --> 00:40:55.810
Unbelievable.

877
00:40:55.887 --> 00:40:59.415
Face it. Shawn. I am and
always will be that good.

878
00:41:00.591 --> 00:41:03.083
That's why my friends in
school used to call me The G.

879
00:41:03.161 --> 00:41:06.495
That's funny. I thought they
called you Bighead Burton.

880
00:41:06.564 --> 00:41:08.055
Don't you ever say that name.

881
00:41:08.132 --> 00:41:09.343
I know it was you
that started that.

882
00:41:09.367 --> 00:41:10.391
I'm sorry. Gus.

883
00:41:10.468 --> 00:41:12.630
I have a knack for
alliteration. I'm a slave to it.

884
00:41:12.704 --> 00:41:15.469
Besides. how many
words start with B. really?

885
00:41:15.540 --> 00:41:16.940
About a thousand.

886
00:41:17.008 --> 00:41:19.307
How about bold.
black. beautiful?

887
00:41:19.377 --> 00:41:20.777
Who's gonna call
you Black Burton?

888
00:41:20.845 --> 00:41:22.177
You get my point. Shawn.

889
00:41:22.246 --> 00:41:23.544
All right.

890
00:41:23.982 --> 00:41:26.542
I'll tell you what. I'm gonna
buy you an ice cream.

891
00:41:26.617 --> 00:41:30.179
and we're gonna discuss some
new fresh-to-death nicknames.

892
00:41:38.262 --> 00:41:42.927
How about Burton.
the Billowy Bear?

893
00:41:46.537 --> 00:41:47.800
What?

894
00:41:49.307 --> 00:41:51.606
Spitballing. It
was my first shot.

895
00:41:59.584 --> 00:42:03.214
<i>In between the lines
there's a lot of obscurity</i>

896
00:42:03.287 --> 00:42:06.724
<i>I'm not inclined to
resign to maturity</i>

897
00:42:06.791 --> 00:42:09.852
<i>If it's all right then
you're all wrong</i>

898
00:42:09.927 --> 00:42:13.557
<i>But why bounce around
to the same damn song?</i>

899
00:42:14.799 --> 00:42:18.861
<i>You'd rather run
when you can't crawl</i>

900
00:42:21.005 --> 00:42:24.464
<i>I know. you know That
I'm not telling the truth</i>

901
00:42:24.542 --> 00:42:27.603
<i>I know. you know They
just don't have any proof</i>

902
00:42:27.678 --> 00:42:30.842
<i>Embrace the deception
Learn how to bend</i>

903
00:42:30.915 --> 00:42:34.909
<i>Your worst inhibitions tend
to psych you out in the end</i>

904
00:42:34.986 --> 00:42:36.682
<i>I know. you know</i>

905
00:42:38.589 --> 00:42:40.217
<i>I know. you know</i>
